- Base case: `([] +' bs) +' cs = [] +' (bs +' cs)`
  - LHS: `([] +' bs) +' cs = bs +' cs` (by definition)
  - RHS: `[] +' (bs +' cs) = bs +' cs` (by definition)
  - These are equal by `rfl`

- Inductive case: `((a :: as) +' bs) +' cs = (a :: as) +' (bs +' cs)`
  - LHS: `((a :: as) +' bs) +' cs = (a :: (as +' bs)) +' cs = a :: ((as +' bs) +' cs)` (by definition)
  - RHS: `(a :: as) +' (bs +' cs) = a :: (as +' (bs +' cs))` (by definition)
  - By inductive hypothesis: `(as +' bs) +' cs = as +' (bs +' cs)`
  - So we can rewrite LHS to get RHS

```lean
example {α : Type*} (as bs cs : List α) :
    (as +' bs) +' cs = as +' (bs +' cs) := by
  induction as with
  | nil => rfl
  | cons a as ih => simp [ih]
